---
import Page from '../layouts/Page.astro';
---

<Page title="about -- alexander campos" description="Alex Campos. 26. Virginia. Software and writing.">
  <article>
    <h1>About</h1>

    <p>
      I'm Alex. 26. Virginia. I build software where you can see how the system sees you.
    </p>

    <p>
      The pattern is always the same: a system builds a model of you,
      compresses it into something useful for the system, and feeds it back.
      Resumes flatten you into keywords. Models compress you into predictions.
      The description becomes the thing.
    </p>

    <p>
      I build the other side of that. Tools where the person owns the model,
      sees the representation, and decides what stays.
    </p>

    <p>
      That's a <a href="https://reframed.works">resume platform</a> that's live
      with payments. An <a href="/projects/forgeframe">open-source memory system</a>
      for AI agents. A <a href="/projects/guardian">desktop app</a> that keeps your
      cognitive data on your machine. Different shapes, same thesis.
    </p>

    <p>
      If you opened the console, you already know the voice.
    </p>

    <h2>Elsewhere</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://github.com/notaprompt">GitHub</a> — open-source work</li>
      <li><a href="https://guardian-labs.org">Guardian Labs</a> — independent research</li>
      <li><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/alexander-d-campos/">LinkedIn</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://substack.com/@alexinthefield">Substack</a> — writing</li>
      <li><a href="#" id="influences-hint">Influences</a> — bookshelf</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      <a href="mailto:alex@campos.works">alex@campos.works</a>
    </p>

  </article>

  <script is:inline>
    console.log(
      '%c same question, different shapes. ',
      'color: #E8DCC8; font-family: monospace; font-size: 11px;'
    );

    // Influences discovery — hint toward the bookshelf on the desk scene
    var hintLink = document.getElementById('influences-hint');
    if (hintLink) {
      hintLink.addEventListener('click', function(e) {
        e.preventDefault();
        var canvas = document.getElementById('desk-scene');
        if (canvas) {
          canvas.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth', block: 'center' });
          // Pulse the tooltip to hint at the bookshelf
          var tip = document.getElementById('ds-tooltip');
          if (tip) {
            tip.textContent = 'bookshelf';
            tip.classList.add('visible');
            setTimeout(function() { tip.classList.remove('visible'); }, 2500);
          }
          // Trigger highlight if desk scene exposes it
          if (window.__highlightDeskObject) {
            window.__highlightDeskObject('books');
          }
        }
      });
    }
  </script>
</Page>
